Pre-Game Insights: Cameroon and Namibia square off in the 2025 Africa Cup of Nations qualifiers on Saturday.
Cameroon head into the weekend unbeaten in their last four competitive home matches.
Namibia were denied a second COSAFA Cup title on July 7 when they fell to a 7-0 loss against Angola.
Namibia were on a six-game unbeaten run across all competitions before their loss to Angola.
Cameroon have named a star-studded squad for September’s qualifiers.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Cameroon hold a slight upper hand in the history of this fixture, having won two of the last four meetings between the two nations.
Namibia have managed one win in that time, which came in March 2023, when they beat Cameroon 2-1 in the AFCON qualifiers.
Cameroon are unbeaten in their last four competitive home games, picking up three wins and one draw since a 1-0 loss against Algeria in March 2022.
Namibia have lost just one of their last seven matches across all competitions while claiming three wins and three draws since June 5.
